    "questions": [
      {
        "question": "Q4-heatmap: Keep the heatmap component (showing kappa values) or drop it?",
        "recommendation": "Keep but rebuild it as a kappa heatmap.",
        "rationale": "Heatmap of pairwise agreement is exactly the right visual for the new data \u2014 color encodes kappa, axes are models. Dropping it loses a useful overview.",
        "updated_at": 1778218313
      }
    ],
    "assumptions": [
      "Reuse existing components and services wherever possible. Do not create new modules unless necessary. Existing snapshot infrastructure, cell accumulator, math/statistics libraries, table/heatmap/section UI components should be extended rather than duplicated.",
      "Equal weighting per cell and per vignette. A cell or vignette with more trials must NOT receive more weight in any aggregate metric (agreement rate, kappa, divergence). Aggregate at cell-level first (e.g. proportion-of-A within cell) then average across cells with equal weight, then average across vignettes with equal weight. This means snapshot must preserve per-cell or per-vignette granularity, not just per-pair totals."
    ],
    "summary": "New section 'Model Agreement on Value Tradeoffs' replaces the 'Statistical Differences in Value Preferences' section on /models. Three stacked scroll-down reports: (1) full-roster pairwise agreement matrix with kappa heatmap, (2) per-model self-consistency, (3) per-value-pair divergence drilldown. Uses Cohen's kappa, percent agreement, and run-to-run reliability (computed across signature-filtered runs). Equal weighting per cell and per vignette \u2014 no observation-count bias. Reuses existing snapshot infrastructure, cell accumulator, math libraries, and UI components; drops p-value and verdict framing entirely.",
    "updated_at": 1778219291,
    "answers": {
      "Q1-scope: Replace just the 'Statistical Differences in Value Preferences' section on /models (leaving cluster analysis intact) or restructure the whole page?": "Replace just the significance section. Cluster analysis and other parts of /models stay unchanged.",
      "Q2-reliability-runs: For run-to-run reliability, use the same runs the signature filter selects, or all completed runs regardless of signature?": "Use the runs selected by the signature filter. Reliability scope matches agreement scope.",
      "Q3-default-view: Default to full-roster pairwise agreement matrix, per-model self-consistency overview, or a specific model pair drilldown?": "No tabs \u2014 three stacked scroll-down sections. Order: (a) Full-roster pairwise agreement matrix first, then (b) per-model self-consistency, then (c) per-pair drilldown.",
      "Q4-heatmap: Keep the heatmap component (showing kappa values) or drop it?": "Adapt the existing heatmap to show kappa values. Reuse the component; just change color scale and tooltip data."
    },
